    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the Chamaecyparis obtusa tree, an evergreen native to Japan and East Asia. Wood is reddish-brown, fragrant, durable and fine grain. It is used for Shinto and Buddhist temples and other construction, furniture, and sculpture.</Note_Text>
